profile_positions.description:
ING Wholesale Banking is leading bank with a local presence in more than 40 countries. It is the first bank in the world to steer its portfolio towards the Paris Climate Agreement and a frontrunner in the green loan markets and provider of sustainability improvement loans. Besides that, ING is accelerating on digitalisation of business and innovation.

I have been working with the RMLA (Reporting, Monitoring, Lending & Analytics) Team and have been performing the following tasks: 
- Champion in Leveraged Transactions in the Corporate Sector Lending department: 
- Helping the bank to continue compliant with regulations and RWAs through lists and exports of our database; Presenting the data to the team in a form of storytelling. 
- Project Manager of the covenant monitoring project, with the goal of make a complete and dynamic database in order to monitor all covenants present in the lending agreements;
- Project Manager of an email covenant tool designed to make the monitoring of covenants more effective; 
- Identifying data quality issues in leveraged transactions and fixing  the problem through the making of remediation packs; 
- Close contact/ Point of contact with the Colombo Team, a team located in Siri Lanka, for a diverse range of projects and set ups. 
- Monitoring standalone intradays, clean down clauses, as well as review dates for credit applications; 
- Performing internal ratings within the company; 
- Hiring of staff: analyzing CVs and participating on interview and decision process of hiring interns; I have analyzed more than 60 CVs & motivation letters, and participated in around 20 interviews. 
- Participated in the Buddy Program of the organization and coached 2 people. 
- Organizing events for team bonding, such as Christmas dinner and MVO event.  
- Completing e-learnings and compliance programs to elevate potential

The Civil Prosecutor's Office represents the Public Prosecutor's Office before the State Court of Justice, observing the respective areas of practice, classified into:
- public records, bankruptcy and corporate recovery;
- family, successions, guardianships and trusteeships;
- writ of mandamus (original jurisdiction and appellate review)
- habeas data, writ of injunction, statute of the child and adolescent, conflict of jurisdiction;
- private law.

The main work of this internship was the elaboration of the legal reports for the cases that fit in one of the above classifications. These reports were attached to the case lawsuit and served to guide the judge in making a decision. Usually, the most common cases I worked on were those involving corporate bankruptcy (and consequently the need for public agency intervention) and those involving underage individuals. Extensive knowledge of Brazilian civil law, procedural law, as well as commercial law was required from me. Besides the opinions, I also worked with research of doctrinal and jurisprudential content, as well as dealing with the different processes that were referred to the office. 

Main accomplishments: as assistant to civil attorney Olavo Antonio de Moraes Freire, I was able to optimize his work, as I did the first analysis and drafts in more than hundreds of cases over the two years I worked there.
